Open old wooden door, The door lock and door frame had come loose. The door creaked loudly when it opened. 
 Crossing the Threshold , What comes into view is a wide open space , It may have once been a warehouse or workshop.

 A few yellowed books lay on an overturned table. , Next to it was a canvas bag with a big hole in it. 
 There are obvious signs of human habitation here.

穿过门槛,映入眼帘的是一片开阔的场地,可能曾经是个仓库或车间。

一张翻倒的桌子上丢着几本泛黄的书,边上是一个破了个大洞的帆布包。

column2:
"Life is getting harder and harder. Food is scarce. I heard that the crazy people in District 13 have started to eat each other." 
 Fat Joe stopped what he was doing and moved closer to you. 
" But I heard there’s a cannery nearby that might still have some.” 
" I tried to go in once, but there were more zombies in there than rats in this whole city, and, the smell…” He wrinkled his nose. 
" If we can get our hands on those cans, we'll be able to survive for a while. But I have to tell you, it's not going to be easy. Those zombies, they... they're not like those roaming the streets, where you'll be stinking for days at a time." 
" Negan once led a large group of people there, but they encountered something and retreated afterwards."

“这日子过得越来越艰难了，食物稀少，听说十三区那帮疯子已经开始互啃了。”
  肥乔停下手中的活计，向你靠近了一些。
“但我听说附近有个罐头加工厂，可能还有存货。”
“我试过一次进去，但那里的僵尸比这整个城市的老鼠还要多，而且，那味道…” 他皱起了鼻子。
“如果我们能搞到那些罐头，至少能撑一阵子。但我得告诉你，那不是件容易的活。那些丧尸，他们…他们不像街上的那些游荡者，被他们沾上臭几天都算少的。”
“尼根曾拉一大帮人过去一次，不知道他们遇到了什么东西，后面都撤回来了。”
